<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:13PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Anson and
southwestern Stanly Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 412 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mint Hill, or 12 miles east of Uptown Charlotte, moving southeast at
20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ansonville, Midland, Polkton, Locust, Oakboro, Stanfield, Peachland
and White Store.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
